    </sec>
    <sec>
      <title>Whole genome analysis for boundaries in <italic>D. melanogaster</italic></title>
      <p><italic>Drosophila melanogaster </italic>genome release 5.2 was used as input for boundary search. Each chromosome was separately analysed using 750 bp as set window size and 10 bp as window slide. Under these conditions, we retrieved 4576 boundaries in the whole genome (<xref ref-type="table" rid="gks045-T3">Table 3</xref> and <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://nar.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/gks045/DC1">Supplementary File S2</ext-link>). cdBEST correctly identified the reported boundaries, even-skipped, TER94, Abd-Bm and myoglianin-eyeless (ME), which were not included in our positive data set (<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="gks045-B43 gks045-B44 gks045-B45 gks045-B46">43–46</xref>). The average domain size deciphered by predicted boundaries varies from 19 to 31 kb for various chromosome arms. Density of predicted boundary was greater on the X chromosome despite having a low gene density and moderate size.
